<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[188,1408,196,739]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
Notes. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jiří Šmíd &amp; Jiří Moravec &amp; Václav Gvoždík &amp; Jan Štundl &amp; Daniel Frynta &amp; Petros Lymberakis &amp; Paschalia Kapli &amp; Thomas Wilms &amp; Andreas Schmitz &amp; Mohammed Shobrak &amp; Saeed Hosseinian Yousefkhani &amp; Eskandar Rastegar-Pouyani &amp; Aurora M. Castilla &amp; Johannes Els &amp; Werner Mayer" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Schenkel" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[285,544,196,224]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Mesalina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bernoullii">
<emphasis box="[285,544,196,224]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Mesalina bernoullii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
represents a morphologically very variable species (
<tableCitation box="[1258,1389,196,224]" captionStart="Table S" captionStartId="29.[102,180,623,652]" captionTargetBox="[210,1856,745,1708]" captionTargetId="graphics@29.[201,1871,726,1707]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="Table S 5. Morphological comparison of Mesalina saudiarabica sp. n. with the other species formerly included under M. brevirostris. Values marked by asterisk indicate subadult specimens." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF130BBDAE4FFFBB5418FDB4A2C46AF9" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" tableUuid="DF130BBDAE4FFFBB5418FDB4A2C46AF9">Table S5</tableCitation>
). Several geographically isolated morphotypes that differ considerably in body size and scalation can be found within its large range. For example, Haas and Werner (1969) assigned a subspecific status (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haas &amp; Werner" authorityYear="1969" box="[469,817,306,334]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Eremias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="brevirostris" subSpecies="fieldi">
<emphasis box="[469,817,306,334]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Eremias brevirostris fieldi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) to the population from south­western 
<collectingCountry box="[1348,1407,306,334]" name="Iran" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Iran</collectingCountry>
characterized by low numbers of dorsal and gular scales and subdigital lamellae and Moravec (2004) described a morphotype from Jabal al Arab, southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1004,1075,380,408]" name="Syria" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Syria</collectingCountry>
, that has unusually high numbers of scales of the same characters. Nevertheless, our results did not show any correlation between this morphological and phylogenetic clustering.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[188,1408,196,739]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
The material analyzed in this study included specimens from the 
<typeStatus box="[1190,1245,490,518]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName authority="Schenkel, 1901" authorityName="Schenkel" authorityYear="1901" box="[188,654,527,555]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Eremias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bernoullii">
<emphasis box="[188,443,527,555]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Eremias bernoullii</emphasis>
Schenkel, 1901
</taxonomicName>
corresponding morphologically to the 
<typeStatus box="[1185,1297,527,555]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">holotype</typeStatus>
of this taxon. It also included a specimen from ca. 
<quantity box="[756,839,564,592]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" unit="km" value="40.0">40 km</quantity>
of the 
<typeStatus box="[932,987,564,592]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName authority="Haas and Werner, 1969" authorityName="Haas and Werner" authorityYear="1969" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Eremias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="brevirostris" subSpecies="fieldi">
<emphasis box="[1138,1400,564,592]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">E. brevirostris fieldi</emphasis>
Haas and Werner, 1969
</taxonomicName>
corresponding morphologically to this form, as well as individuals representing the Jabal al Arab morphotype. Based on the results of the phylogenetic and morphological analyses we conclude that the name 
<taxonomicName authority="Haas and Werner, 1969" authorityName="Haas and Werner" authorityYear="1969" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Eremias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="brevirostris" subSpecies="fieldi">
<emphasis box="[904,1266,674,702]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Eremias brevirostris fieldi</emphasis>
Haas and Werner, 1969
</taxonomicName>
is a junior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Schenkel, 1901" authorityName="Schenkel" authorityYear="1901" box="[806,1256,711,739]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Eremias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bernoullii">
<emphasis box="[806,1055,711,739]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Eremias bernoullii</emphasis>
Schenkel, 1901
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
